FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOver%208%2C000%20authors%20signed%20a%20letter%20saying%20the%20AI%20industry%20uses%20their%20work%20without%20permission.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThey're%20telling%20companies%20to%20%26quot%3Bmitigate%20the%20damage%26quot%3B%20to%20their%20profession%20caused%20by%20generative%20AI.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThere%20has%20been%20deepening%20criticism%20of%20AI%20companies%20from%20across%20the%20media%20and%20entertainment%20industries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%208%2C000%20authors%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Margaret%20Atwood%20and%20James%20Patterson%20%E2%80%94%20have%20signed%20an%20open%20letter%20demanding%20compensation%20from%20AI%20companies%20for%20using%20their%20works%20to%20train%20AI%20without%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMillions%20of%20copyrighted%20books%2C%20articles%2C%20essays%2C%20and%20poetry%20provide%20the%20%26quot%3Bfood%26quot%3B%20for%20AI%20systems%2C%20endless%20meals%20for%20which%20there%20has%20been%20no%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20authors%20wrote%20in%20a%20letter%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Factionnetwork.org%2Fpetitions%2Fauthors-guild-open-letter-to-generative-ai-leaders%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Epublished%20by%20the%20Authors%20Guild%20on%20Tuesday%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%20is%20addressed%20to%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%2C%20Alphabet%20CEO%20Sundar%20Pichai%2C%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20Stability%20AI%20CEO%20Emad%20Mostaque%2C%20IBM%20CEO%20Arvind%20Krishna%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Satya%20Nadella.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20result%20of%20embedding%20our%20writings%20in%20your%20systems%2C%20generative%20AI%20threatens%20to%20damage%20our%20profession%20by%20flooding%20the%20market%20with%20mediocre%2C%20machine-written%20books%2C%20stories%2C%20and%20journalism%20based%20on%20our%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20letter%20reads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPer%20the%20letter%2C%20authors%20have%20seen%20a%2040%25%20drop%20in%20earnings%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20with%20full-time%20writers'%20median%20income%20in%202022%20being%20just%20%2423%2C330%2C%20the%20Authors%20Guild's%20found%20after%20surveying%20over%205%2C700%20participants.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Authors%20Guild%20says%20AI%20technology%20will%20make%20it%20even%20harder%20for%20writers%20to%20make%20a%20living.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20letter's%20over%208%2C000%20signatories%20%E2%80%94%20including%20%26quot%3BThe%20Da%20Vinci%20Code%26quot%3B%20author%20Dan%20Brown%20and%20%26quot%3BThe%20Hunger%20Games%26quot%3B%20writer%20Suzanne%20Collins%20%E2%80%94%20want%20AI%20companies%20to%20%26quot%3Bmitigate%20the%20damage%20to%20our%20profession%26quot%3B%20by%20providing%20compensation%20for%20past%20and%20future%20uses%20of%20their%20writing%2C%20per%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20systems%20are%20trained%20on%20large%20volumes%20of%20data%2C%20much%20of%20which%20is%20text%20scraped%20from%20the%20internet.%20However%2C%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20companies%20have%20legally%20obtained%20permissions%20for%20this%20AI%20training%20remains%20unclear%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fthousands-of-authors-ask-ai-chatbot-owners-to-pay-for-use-of-their-work-9c6198b1%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%2C%20Google%2C%20Meta%2C%20Stability%20AI%2C%20IBM%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20from%20Insider.%20OpenAI%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20to%20the%20Journal%20that%20ChatGPT%20is%20trained%20on%20%26quot%3Blicensed%20content%2C%20publicly%20available%20content%2C%20and%20content%20created%20by%20human%20AI%20trainers%20and%20users%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20the%20company%20respects%20the%20rig