2C%20354D%20(stalking)%20and%20506%20(criminal%20intimidation)%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETomar%20was%20charged%20with%20offences%20under%20IPC%20sections%20109%20(abetment%20of%20any%20offence%2C%20if%20the%20act%20abetted%20is%20committed%20in%20consequence%2C%20and%20where%20no%20express%20provision%20is%20made%20for%20its%20punishment)%2C%20354%2C%20354A%20and%20506%20(criminal%20intimidation).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20case%20registered%20by%20six%20women%20wrestlers%2C%20another%20first%20information%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fwrestlers-protest-brij-bhushan-sharan-singh-withdraw-complaint-minor-pocso%5C%22%3Ewas%20registered%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20Singh%20by%20a%20minor%20grappler%2C%20which%20was%20registered%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20(POCSO)%20Act.%20She%20was%20among%20the%20seven%20female%20wrestlers%20who%20had%20accused%20Singh%20of%20sexual%20harassment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20been%20the%20primary%20concern%20of%20protesting%20wrestlers%20that%20a%20man%20booked%20under%20POCSO%2C%20which%20calls%20for%20immediate%20action%2C%20had%20not%20been%20arrested.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegations%20against%20Singh%20include%20inappropriate%20touching%2C%20groping%2C%20stalking%20and%20intimidation%20by%20him%20at%20different%20times%20and%20places%20over%20a%20decade.%20Other%20allegations%20against%20him%20include%20dictatorial%20functioning%20and%20financial%20irregularities%20in%20the%20management%20of%20WFI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minor%E2%80%99s%20complaint%2C%20however%2C%20was%20later%20changed.%20Olympic%20medallist%20Sakshi%20Malik%20had%20said%20the%20minor%20had%20changed%20her%20statement%20because%20%E2%80%9Cher%20family%20was%20threatened%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20%3Cem%3ETelegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraphindia.com%2Findia%2Fminor-wrestler-changed-statement-because-her-family-was-threatened-says-sakshi-malik%2Fcid%2F1945863%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20elections%20to%20the%20WFI%20%E2%80%93%20a%20key%20promise%20made%20by%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20top%20wrestlers%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fwrestling-federation-of-india-elections-face-further-delay%5C%22%3Eare%20facing%20further%20delays.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsport%2Fwrestling-federation-of-india-elections-face-further-delay%5C%22%3Epromises%3C%2Fa%3E%20made%20to%20the%20wrestlers%20by%20the%20Union%20sports%20minister%2C%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20were%20fresh%20elections%20to%20select%20leadership%20for%20the%20federation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20WFI%20elections%20were%20originally%20scheduled%20for%20July%2011.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20election%20was%20initially%20stayed%20by%20the%20Gauhati%20high%20court%20after%20the%20Assam%20Wrestling%20Association%20sought%20to%20be%20included%20in%20the%20electoral%20college%20as%20a%20state%20unit%20of%20the%20WFI.%20The%20high%20court%2C%20a%20day%20ago%2C%20said%20that%20the%20next%20hearing%20would%20be%20on%20July%2028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-removes-gauhati-hcs-stay-of-wrestling-federation-elections%5C%22%3Eremoved%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20stay%20imposed%20by%20the%20high%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20still%20not%20clear%20if%20the%20elections%20can%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689681014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F28201406%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-05-28-at-8.13.23-PM.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcourt-grants-interim-bail-to-brij-bhushan-singh-in-wrestlers-sexual-harassment-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22He%20was%20asked%20to%20furnish%20a%20personal%20bon